title: Kenyans Dominate Men's Event at Jakarta Marathon
text:
Kenyans Dominate Men's Event at Jakarta Marathon i Indonesian athlete Agus Prayogo did not make it to the podium on Sunday. (Antara Photo/Yudhi Mahatma) By : Hendro Situmorang | on 11:22 AM October 25, 2015 Category : Sports , Athletics 
Jakarta. Kenyan runner Geoffrey Kiprotich Birgen took the gold in the Jakarta Marathon on Sunday, taking two hours, 17 minutes and 38 seconds to cover the distance in the Indonesian capital, while Indonesia's own Supriyati Sutono was the first woman to finish, in three hours, 16 minutes and 32 seconds. 
Some 15,000 people took part in the event, with runners being able to choose from a variety of distances: the full marathon (42.195 kilometers), half marathon, ten kilometers or five kilometers. 
There was also a "Maratoonz" sprint event for children. 
In the men's marathon, Kenyans Josphat Kiptanui Too Chobei (2:18:22) and Luka Chelimo Kipkemboi (2:19:54) finished second and third. 
In the women's category, Indonesian athletes Rumini Sudrami (3:22:04) and Raquel Pirera (3:29:10) took second and third place. 
Because of the marathon, several roads in the city center had been closed from midnight till 10 a.m.
